                  <additions>
                    <list>
                      <item xml:id="a01">
                      <desc type="GuestText">
                      <locus target="#iii(erso)"/> Introduction to the Psalms
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e01">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#ir #iv"/> pen trials
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e02">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#iir(ecto)"/> blank
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e03">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#iiir(ecto)"/> The psalter was begun on this folio, but abandoned and erased and begun again on <locus target="#1r"/>
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e04">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#ivr(ecto)"/>: scrawls
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e05">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#45v"/> A two-word text “here is half” surrounded in red and black ink, marks the midpoint of the psalms
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a02">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#113v"/> beginning of Trinitarian formula
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e06">
                      <desc>
                      Psalm 118 has the spiritual meaning of the Hebrew letters
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e07">
                      <desc>
                      The back cover has a recessed niche in which there was probably a mirror at one time
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e08">
                      <desc>
                      words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#3v #9r #23v #31v"/>, etc.);
                      and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#25r #31v #37r #56v"/>, etc.);
                      and in the upper margin with a symbol (+) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (<locus target="#37r"/>, line 11);
                      erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#8v #88v"/>);
                      text has been removed (e.g., <locus target="#70v"/>)
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e09">
                      <desc>
                      The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an appropriate
                      aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. Where the line is still too long, the scribe completes the line of text above
                      or below the end of the line (throughout)
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                    </list>
